                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17510116-55-off259 t17510116-55-cd260"></join>.* </p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17510116-55-person497">
                  Samuel 
                  Mills 
               <interp inst="t17510116-55-person497" type="surname" value="Mills"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510116-55-person497" type="given" value="Samuel"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510116-55-person497" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner come down my master's stairs January the 7th, with a bag of sugar on his back, about two in the afternoon.</p>
               <p>Q. Who is your master?</p>
               <p>Mills. 
               <persName id="t17510116-55-person498">
                  David 
                  Day 
               <interp inst="t17510116-55-person498" type="surname" value="Day"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510116-55-person498" type="given" value="David"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510116-55-person498" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , my lord; I took him under the gateway, and asked him what he had got in his bag; he drop'd the bag and run away; I pursued and took him, and brought him back to the compting-house : he told me he got this sugar up three pair of stairs, in a place called little ease, there was a hogshead broken up. I compared the sugar that he had with that and it agreed; he was carried before an alderman and committed.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17510116-55-person499">
                  James 
                  Emerson 
               <interp inst="t17510116-55-person499" type="surname" value="Emerson"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510116-55-person499" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510116-55-person499" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am constable. I was charged with the prisoner, he owned the fact to me.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>I was hired as a <rs id="t17510116-55-deflabel261" type="occupation">porter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17510116-55-defend493 t17510116-55-deflabel261"></join>, and this man came and took the sugar off my back; I was then in liquor, and did not then know what it was, and I drop'd it and went to go away, and they cry'd stop thief, and brought me back.</p>
